reviews.text: Food was fine, good British pub grub. Nothing fancy. Prices felt a little on the high side but manageable. Service was friendly and reasonable. Not a bad choice if that is what you are looking for. Nice view of Victoria harbor. I would consider going again.
Very caring service. Nice steak. Dessert was a bit too sweet for me but overall it tasted good. Drinks were awesome as well.

Stayed here for a quick supper.  Service is exceptionally good.  Very caring staff.  We ordered slow cooked pork rib which is really tender and well cooked.  Seasoning is just right, not too sweet.  

The toffee pudding is a little bit too sweet for me but nice.

Overall,  asn't ruined Gordon's name.

Did is stunning and delivered quickly. Drinks are strong and very reasonably priced with high quality. The decor is very fitting for the theme, and there is also live music during the weekend to liven the visits up a bit. Strong recommendation, but if you are going with a crowd during the weekend a reservation might be needed as the place gets very busy.

Friendly atmosphere, good place for casual to semi business dining.  We are a group on 20, we sat outside,as a few of us are smokers.  Despite its outside, its sheltered.  You will be fine if it drizzles.  Prices of foods are reasonable, but drinks are in average >$80 per glass.  Their staff acted efficiently once they see you are about to finish your drink.
